<plot>EXHIBIT A: Leary Vs. Hicks is an experimental documentary meditation on the dangers of artistic theft in the world of stand-up comedy, and an expose on the little-known yet long-standing allegation that performer 'Denis Leary' (qv) lifted much of his persona and act from fellow comedian 'Bill Hicks (II)' (qv). Culled from hours of archive footage and presented here for the first time ever, the similarities in question are shown back-to-back allowing audiences to decide for themselves.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?185273</url></doc>
